function validSquare(p1, p2, p3, p4) {
    function distSq(p, q) {
        return (p[0] - q[0]) ** 2 + (p[1] - q[1]) ** 2;
    }

    let points = [p1, p2, p3, p4];
    let dists = new Set();

    for (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < 4; j++) {
            dists.add(distSq(points[i], points[j]));
        }
    }

    return dists.size === 2 && !dists.has(0);
}
```

    1. Create a function to calculate the distance between two points in 2D space.
2. Create a set to store unique distances between points.
3. Iterate through all distinct pairs of points, calculating the distance between them and adding the result to the set.
4. Check if the size of the set is 2, meaning that there are exactly two unique distances, and that the smallest distance is not 0, indicating that no two points are the same.
5. If the above conditions are met, the four points form a square. Otherwise, they do not.

